{{Citation needed|date=May 14, 2013}} '''Saho no Ōkurami Tome''' (沙本之大闇見戸売) is a female figure mentioned in the {{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀|12=draft|12=draft}}. She was the consort of {{ill|Hikoimasu no Mikoto|ja|彦坐王|12=draft|12=draft}} (Prince Hikoimasu, son of {{ill|Emperor Kaika|ja|開化天皇|12=draft|12=draft}}). She bore the following children: {{ill|Sahohiko no Ō|ja|狭穂彦王|1=Sahohiko no Mikoto|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Onyaho no Mikoto|ja|袁邪本王|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Murobiko no Mikoto|ja|室毘古|12=draft|12=draft}}, and [[Saho-hime]] (later Empress of {{ill|Emperor Suinin|ja|垂仁天皇|12=draft|12=draft}}).
Her mother was known as Kasuga no Takekuni Katsutome (春日建国勝戸売), a name that suggests her lineage was closely tied to the {{ill|Kasuga|ja|春日野|12=draft|12=draft}} and Saho regions, encompassing the northern part of the {{ill|Yamato Basin|ja|大和盆地|12=draft|12=draft}}. This indicates she likely belonged to a powerful local clan in that area.
== Shrine Location ==
* {{ill|Yamimi Shrine|ja|闇見神社|12=draft|12=draft}}, located in {{ill|Wakasa, Fukui|ja|福井県三方上中郡若狭町|12=draft|12=draft}} (12-7, Tearuimizu, Jōganji, Wakasa, Fukui Prefecture).
== References == * Tsukaguchi, Yoshinobu. *Exploring the Mysteries of Yamatai and Early Yamato Authority*. Harashobo, 2016.
{{Japanese-history-stub}}
