{{Infobox person|gender={{ill|female|qid=Q6581072}}|spouse={{ill|Hikoimasu|qid=Q11487910}}|children={{ill|Empress Sahohime|qid=Q11571754}}; {{ill|Prince Sahohiko|qid=Q11571755}}; {{ill|Q11626514|qid=Q11626514}}}}{{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[d:Q13360104]] Wikidata name: (none) [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 09:00, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} {{Citation needed|date=May 14, 2013}} '''Saho no Ōkurami Tome''' (沙本之大闇見戸売) is a female figure mentioned in the [[:en:Kojiki|Kojiki]] and [[:en:Nihon Shoki|Nihon Shoki]]. She was the consort of {{ill|Hikoimasu no Ōkimi|lt=Hikoimasu no Ōkimi|lt=Hikoimasu no Mikoto|ja|彦坐王|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hikoimasu no Mikoto|qq=}} (Prince Hikoimasu, son of [[:en:Emperor Kaika|Emperor Kaika]]). She bore the following children: {{ill|Sahohiko no Ō|ja|狭穂彦王|1=Sahohiko no Mikoto|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sahohiko no Ō|13=User:Immanuelle/Sahohiko no Mikoto|qq=}}, {{ill|Ozaho no Ōkimi|lt=Ozaho no Ōkimi|lt=Onyaho no Mikoto|ja|袁邪本王|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onyaho no Mikoto|qq=}}, {{ill|Murobiko no Mikoto|ja|室毘古|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Murobiko no Mikoto|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, and [[Saho-hime]] (later Empress of [[:en:Emperor Suinin|Emperor Suinin]]).
Her mother was known as Kasuga no Takekuni Katsutome (春日建国勝戸売), a name that suggests her lineage was closely tied to the {{ill|Kasuga|ja|春日野|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kasuga|qq=|1=Kasuga|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11513714}} and Saho regions, encompassing the northern part of the {{ill|Yamato Basin|ja|大和盆地|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamato Basin|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 奈良盆地|1=Nara Basin|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q10942269}}. This indicates she likely belonged to a powerful local clan in that area.
== Shrine Location ==
* {{ill|Yamimi Shrine|ja|闇見神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamimi Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, located in {{ill|Wakasa, Fukui|ja|福井県三方上中郡若狭町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakasa, Fukui|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (12-7, Tearuimizu, Jōganji, Wakasa, Fukui Prefecture).
== References == * Tsukaguchi, Yoshinobu. *Exploring the Mysteries of Yamatai and Early Yamato Authority*. Harashobo, 2016.
